data.text: She appeared in campaigns for companies including L.K.Bennett, Abercrombie & Fitch, Lacoste, Burberry, Topshop and posed for InStyle, Cosmopolitan, Vogue, and Nylon. Gabriella made her modeling career debut at age 14 and joined Naomi Campbell’s agency Premier Model Management. In 2014, she starred in the remake of Endless Love, opposite Alex Pettyfer. She began filming in June 2012 and it was released in October 2013. She was cast in the ABC Sci-Fi television pilot Dark Horse in March 2012 and in the MGM and Screen Gems’ remake, Carrie, that same month. Gabriella smuggled vodka into Heathfield, resulting in suspension and a transfer to St Swithun’s. Afterward, Gabriella attended Heathfield St Mary’s School, Ascot, and St Swithun’s School, Winchester, before leaving to pursue a course in art while continuing with her modeling career. Gabriella and her future husband were both educated at Windlesham House School. Gabriella is 32 years old as of 2021, she was born on April 8, 1989, in Basingstoke, United Kingdom as Gabriella Zanna Vanessa Anstruther-Gough-Calthorpe. Her television work includes the Doctor Who episode “The Vampires of Venice” (2010) as well as the BBC historical drama series Poldark (2016–2019). Gabriella has appeared in the films St Trinian’s 2: The Legend of Fritton’s Gold (2009), The Three Musketeers (2011), Carrie (2013), Endless Love (2014), and Wonder Woman 1984 (2020). Gabriella Wilde, known professionally as Gabriella Calthorpe, is an English model and actress who was born on April 8, 1989, in Basingstoke, United Kingdom as Gabriella Zanna Vanessa Anstruther-Gough-Calthorpe.
